sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist Browser
    participant OAuth as OpenShift OAuth<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+ Edge
    participant Proxy as OAuth Proxy Sidecar<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant Jupyter as JupyterLab Container<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant ModelReg as Model Registry<br/>8080/TCP HTTP mTLS
    participant KFP as Kubeflow Pipelines<br/>8888/TCP HTTP mTLS

    Note over User,Jupyter: Flow 1: Notebook Launch and Access

    User->>OAuth: GET /notebook/{namespace}/{user}/<br/>OAuth2 Authentication
    OAuth-->>User: OAuth2 Bearer Token
    User->>Route: GET /notebook/{namespace}/{user}/<br/>Bearer Token
    Route->>Proxy: Forward Request<br/>TLS Termination
    Proxy->>Proxy: Validate OAuth2 Token
    Proxy->>Jupyter: HTTP Request (localhost)<br/>No encryption
    Jupyter-->>Proxy: JupyterLab UI HTML
    Proxy-->>Route: Response
    Route-->>User: HTTPS Response

    Note over User,S3: Flow 2: Model Training and Storage

    User->>Jupyter: Execute training code<br/>via JupyterLab
    Jupyter->>K8sAPI: GET /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/secrets<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Jupyter: AWS credentials
    Jupyter->>S3: GET /bucket/dataset<br/>AWS SigV4 Auth
    S3-->>Jupyter: Training data
    Jupyter->>Jupyter: Train model
    Jupyter->>S3: PUT /bucket/model.pkl<br/>AWS SigV4 Auth
    S3-->>Jupyter: 200 OK
    Jupyter->>ModelReg: POST /api/v1/models<br/>mTLS + ServiceAccount Token
    ModelReg-->>Jupyter: Model registered

    Note over Jupyter,KFP: Flow 3: Pipeline Execution (Elyra Runtime)

    User->>Jupyter: Submit pipeline via Elyra UI
    Jupyter->>KFP: POST /apis/v1beta1/runs<br/>mTLS + ServiceAccount Token
    KFP-->>Jupyter: Pipeline run created
    KFP->>K8sAPI: Create Runtime Image Pod<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>KFP: Pod created
    Note over KFP: Runtime Image executes<br/>pipeline steps
    KFP->>S3: GET /bucket/input<br/>AWS SigV4 Auth
    S3-->>KFP: Input data
    KFP->>S3: PUT /bucket/output<br/>AWS SigV4 Auth
    S3-->>KFP: 200 OK

    Note over User,K8sAPI: Flow 4: Image Pull and Deployment

    User->>Route: Request new notebook
    Route->>K8sAPI: Create Notebook CR<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI->>K8sAPI: Notebook Controller watches
    K8sAPI->>K8sAPI: Read ImageStream
    K8sAPI->>K8sAPI: Create StatefulSet
    Note over K8sAPI: Kubelet pulls image<br/>from quay.io/modh/*<br/>using Image Pull Secret
    K8sAPI-->>User: Notebook pod running
